us.ba3.me.virtualmaps

Class TileProviderRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • us.ba3.me.virtualmaps.TileProviderRequest

  • public class TileProviderRequest
extends java.lang.Object
    Sent to tile providers when tile resources are needed for virtual maps.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      CoordinateBounds bounds
      The geographic bounds of the tile being requested.
      java.lang.String cachedImageName
      The name of a previously cached image.
      boolean compressTexture
      Whether or not returned raster data should be compresses to a lossy 2-byte format.
      java.lang.String fileName
      If you supply an image file, this will be the full path of the file.
      BitmapSimple image
      For non-spherical mercator maps, the image you want to use for this tile.
      boolean isOpaque
      If set, tells the mapping engine that every pixel of the tile is lit and has no semi-transparent pixels.
      TileProviderResponse responseType
      The response from the tile provider which determines what the mapping engine does.
      SphericalMercatorRasterTile[] sphericalMercatorRasterTiles
      For spherical mercator maps, this will be an array of spherical mercator tiles you must 'fill in' with images.

      • isOpaque

        public boolean isOpaque
        If set, tells the mapping engine that every pixel of the tile is lit and has no semi-transparent pixels. This allows the engine to optimize storage and layering of the tile (i.e. no tile underneath this tile will be visible if it is opaque.
